@startuml Signaling & WebRTC Session
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5

title DVConf — Signaling & WebRTC Media Flow

actor "User A\n(Creator)" as A
actor "User B\n(Joiner)" as B
participant "Client A" as CA
participant "Client B" as CB
participant "Signaling\nNode" as Sig
participant "Relay Node\n(mediasoup)" as Relay
database "Sui Chain" as Chain

== Pre-Session: Room Ready ==

note over CA, Chain
  Room already created, CP assigned
  relay + signaling. Client resolved
  endpoint URLs via devInspect.
end note

== Signaling Connection ==

CA -> Sig : WebSocket connect
CA -> Sig : { type: "join",\n  roomId, peerId: A }
Sig -> Sig : rooms[roomId].add(A)
Sig --> CA : { type: "peer-list",\n  peers: [] }

CB -> Sig : WebSocket connect
CB -> Sig : { type: "join",\n  roomId, peerId: B }
Sig -> Sig : rooms[roomId].add(B)
Sig --> CB : { type: "peer-list",\n  peers: [A] }
Sig --> CA : { type: "peer-joined",\n  peerId: B }

== WebRTC Setup via Relay (SFU Mode) ==

CA -> Relay : Create send transport\n(mediasoup-client)
Relay --> CA : transport params\n(id, iceParams, dtlsParams)

CA -> Relay : Produce audio/video track
Relay --> CA : producerId

CB -> Relay : Create send transport
Relay --> CB : transport params

CB -> Relay : Create recv transport
Relay --> CB : transport params

note over Sig
  Signaling relays SDP offers/answers
  and ICE candidates between peers
  for transport negotiation
end note

CA -> Sig : { type: "offer", to: B, sdp }
Sig -> CB : { type: "offer", from: A, sdp }
CB -> Sig : { type: "answer", to: A, sdp }
Sig -> CA : { type: "answer", from: B, sdp }

CA -> Sig : { type: "ice-candidate",\n  to: B, candidate }
Sig -> CB : forward ICE candidate
CB -> Sig : { type: "ice-candidate",\n  to: A, candidate }
Sig -> CA : forward ICE candidate

== Media Flowing (SFU) ==

note over CA, Relay
  **SFU Mode**: Each user sends 1 stream
  to relay. Relay fans out to all others.
  No mixing — each receiver gets
  individual streams.
end note

CA -> Relay : audio/video stream →
Relay -> CB : ← fan-out A's stream

CB -> Relay : audio/video stream →
Relay -> CA : ← fan-out B's stream

note over Relay
  Relay tracks metrics:
  • packets_forwarded
  • bytes_transferred
  • unique_peers
  • latency / jitter
  Exposed via GET /metrics?roomId=xxx
end note

== Peer Disconnect ==

B -> CB : Leave room
CB -> Sig : { type: "leave",\n  roomId, peerId: B }
Sig -> Sig : rooms[roomId].remove(B)
Sig --> CA : { type: "peer-left",\n  peerId: B }

CB -> Relay : Close transports

@enduml
